From: Dave Airlie <airlied@redhat.com>
Date: Thu, 24 Sep 2020 15:18:05 +1000
Subject: [PATCH 0121/1714] drm/nouveau/ttm: handle ttm moves properly.
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

The idea is to flip the core over to calling the driver always,
so add support for moves here.

Signed-off-by: Dave Airlie <airlied@redhat.com>
Acked-by: Christian KÃ¶nig <christian.koenig@amd.com>
Reviewed-by: Ben Skeggs <bskeggs@redhat.com>
Signed-off-by: Dave Airlie <airlied@redhat.com>
Link: https://patchwork.freedesktop.org/patch/msgid/20200924051845.397177-6-airlied@gmail.com
---
 drivers/gpu/drm/nouveau/nouveau_bo.c | 12 ++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 12 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/nouveau/nouveau_bo.c b/drivers/gpu/drm/nouveau/nouveau_bo.c
index 823be16154c8..8ebc2261bbde 100644
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/nouveau/nouveau_bo.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/nouveau/nouveau_bo.c
@@ -1056,6 +1056,18 @@ nouveau_bo_move(struct ttm_buffer_object *bo, bool evict,
 		goto out;
 	}
 
+	if (old_reg->mem_type == TTM_PL_SYSTEM &&
+	    new_reg->mem_type == TTM_PL_TT) {
+		ttm_bo_move_null(bo, new_reg);
+		goto out;
+	}
+
+	if (old_reg->mem_type == TTM_PL_TT &&
+	    new_reg->mem_type == TTM_PL_SYSTEM) {
+		ret = ttm_bo_move_ttm(bo, ctx, new_reg);
+		goto out;
+	}
+
 	/* Hardware assisted copy. */
 	if (drm->ttm.move) {
 		if (new_reg->mem_type == TTM_PL_SYSTEM)
